98/320 Monday 3rd August 1998
MONTHLY CREUTZFELDT-JAKOB DISEASE FIGURES

The Department of Health is today issuing the latest monthly table, giving
the numbers of deaths of definite and probable cases of Creutzfeldt-Jakob
disease in the UK.

Year Referrals Deaths of definite and probable cases in the UK

Sporadi Iatroge Familia GSS nvCJD Total

1985 - 26 1 1 0 - 28
1986 - 26 0 0 0 - 26
1987 - 23 0 0 1 - 24
1988 - 22 1 1 0 - 24
1989 - 28 2 2 0 - 32
1990 53 28 5 0 0 - 33
1991 75 32 1 3 0 - 36
1992 96 44 2 4 1 - 51
1993 78 38 4 2 2 - 46
1994 116 51 1 4 3 - 59
1995 86 34 4 2 3 3 46
1996 134 41 4 2 4 10 61
1997 157 55 6 3 0 10 74
1998* 58 13 0 1 0 4 18

* To 30 June 1998. Total number of definite and probable cases of nvCJD = 27.

The next table will be published on 7 September 1998.
